HEADWORD: Circumrotation
<hw>Cir`cum*ro*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
rolling or revolving round, as a wheel; circumvolution; the state of
being whirled round.</def> <rj><au>J. Gregory.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumscissile</ent>⟦br⟧
